President Obama has declared a major disaster in Oklahoma due to severe storms and flooding that occurred from June 11-13, 2016. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts. The funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Charles Maskell has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and based on damage assessments.